				<li id="16753043" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1660016020000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579630/Loretta's-War-Sickle" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Aug 2022 23:33</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16753043" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Such a theoretically cool weapon with an amazing look and moveset that can&apos;t really find its place. Its only benefit over the Guardian Swordspear is reach. Otherwise, Swordspear has the build variety, lower stat requirements, customizable ashes, etc.<br/><br/>Even on a 20/50/50 Str/Dex/Int build that Loretta is specifically built for, the Swordspear hits nearly the same AR on Magic infusion (729 vs 736). And if you shift stats to be full Int at 20/16/80, you have 4 stats leftover compared to 50/50, full access to sorceries, and slightly higher AR on the Swordspear (745; Loretta is 658 at those stats). The only way I could see Loretta winning out is a 50/50/50 build, and at that point, Swordspear might win out anyway on a physical infusion + Scholar&apos;s Armament.<br/><br/>I want to love this weapon, but even building specifically for it is subpar.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16753043" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16753043" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href="